each router generates a server descriptor and uploads it to each authority
each authority computes and signs a combined consensus status document from the votes given by the other authorities
each authority periodically aggregates all the descriptors into a "status-vote", signs it, and sends it to the other authorities
each authority then serves this consensus to clients. This consensus is also served by directory cache routers
